{"slug": "sigil", "root": "sigil", "category": "item", "gloss": "a drawn magical symbol", "definition": "A sigil is a drawn magical sign — a symbol, often a compressed name or figure, inscribed to focus or command a power. It is the magician's mark.", "history": "Latin *sigillum*, 'a little sign or seal,' diminutive of *signum*, 'sign' (the root of *signal* and *signature*). In the Solomonic tradition each spirit has its sigil, its seal of binding; RenaissanceMagicDB catalogues the *characteres* inscribed on talismans and pentacles, and John Dee's *Sigillum Dei Aemeth* is the tradition's masterpiece. Magic uses 'Sigil' widely for enchantments and tokens.", "def_sources": [{"label": "Etymonline, s.v. sigil", "where": "Etymology reference"}, {"label": "RenaissanceMagicDB, s.v. characteres", "where": "RenaissanceMagicDB"}], "is_keyword": false, "etymology": {"origin": "Latin sigillum ‘little sign/seal’, diminutive of signum ‘sign’", "first": "1650s", "note": "A sigil is a ‘little seal’ — a sign compressed into a mark of power. Same root as ‘signal’ and ‘signature.’", "hook": "How a signature becomes a spell.", "lang": "Latin"}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 19, "oracle_total": 3, "in_flavor_cards": 19, "in_oracle_cards": 2, "name_match_count": 16, "by_variant": {"sigil": 15, "sigils": 7}, "first_year": 1995, "colors": {"U": 8, "W": 19, "R": 1, "C": 2, "G": 8, "B": 7}, "by_year": {"1995": 1, "2006": 1, "2008": 6, "2009": 5, "2011": 1, "2012": 1, "2015": 2, "2016": 1, "2017": 1, "2018": 3, "2019": 1, "2020": 1, "2022": 4, "2023": 1, "2024": 2, "2025": 1}}, "cards": [{"id": "98388eba-31ab-4302-be9e-ea67ea2b8c1a", "name": "Leshrac's Sigil", "set": "ICE", "set_name": "Ice Age", "released": "1995-06-03", "type_line": "Enchantment", "rarity": "uncommon", "colors": ["B"], 